President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Mississippi due to severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding on April 12, 2020. This declaration makes Federal funding available to affected individuals in the counties of Covington, Jefferson Davis, and Jones. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs for recovery. Federal funding is also available for emergency protective measures and hazard mitigation statewide. Jose M. Girot has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional assistance may be designated after the assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance starting tomorrow through the DisasterAssistance.gov website or by calling FEMA. The toll-free telephone numbers will operate from 7 a.m. to 10 p.m. seven days a week. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.